-- Iran May Increase Electricity Prices by 20% in March, Mehr Says
-- B y   L a d a n e   N a s s e r i
-- 2012-01-29T06:47:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-29/iran-may-increase-electricity-prices-by-20-in-march-mehr-says.html
Iran  may raise electricity prices by
about 20 percent in March as part of a plan to cut energy
subsidies, state-run  Mehr  reported, citing Mohammad Behzad,
deputy energy minister  Iran in December 2010 started a five-year plan to phase out
subsidies on fuel, electricity and basic  consumer goods ,
replacing them with cash payments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladane Nasseri in Tehran at 
 lnasseri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  